    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About ALSO.\n\nWe’re ALSO, an electric mobility company originally conceived as a part of Rivian. We’re a passionate team of builders, dreamers, doers and innovators, focused on creating entirely new (not to mention, innovative and delightful) vertically integrated, small EVs designed to meet the global mobility challenges of today and tomorrow. Our mission is to inspire everyone to ride ALSO—replacing many local car, truck and SUV miles with ones on vehicles that are more affordable, more enjoyable and 10-50x more efficient.\n\nALSO. is looking for a Vehicle CAD Lead, Integration Engineer to own and drive the top level master CAD assembly for new vehicle platforms. This is a rare opportunity to have a front row seat and high level impact on each new vehicle product from two to four wheeled.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n - Lead end to end development of top level CAD assemblies in CATIA facilitating team wide design iteration and release activities.\n\n - Direct ownership of top level vehicle CAD including definition of mechanical and electrical interfaces, skeletons, hardpoints, maintain master sections and reference views, kinematic sweeps of steering and suspension components, etc\n\n - Lead Cross-Functional Packaging Workstreams including development of subsystem control volumes and interfaces, mass optimization, packaging, manufacturability, and serviceability.\n\n - Lead Interference Detection and Resolution activities through frequent manual and automated interference checks. Manage interference resolution by tracking issue status and driving collaboration between subsystem engineering teams.\n\n - Orchestrate Vehicle Level Assembly Simulations to detect clearance, assembly flight path, tool access and serviceability issues.\n\nOrganize and Drive PLM Integration Activities. Manage top level CAD data lifecycle and audit subsystem lifecycle status. Create and develop top level vehicle BOM and manage handoff within PLM tools.\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n - Exceptional spatial reasoning and design creativity coupled with CATIA specific CAD best practices and tools\n\n - Strong collaboration and communication skills - you enjoy and thrive in an environment work working with wide range of engineers and stakeholders to solve problems and agree on consistent approaches and first principles in that problem solving\n\n - Broad technical knowledge in order to engage thoughtfully across the range of typical vehicle design technical disciplines: general spacial reasoning and graphical communication, structures, mechanism kinematics, manufacturing tooling approaches, thermal systems, electrical module and harness integration and more.\n\n - Expertise and track record in similar roles in industries such as automotive, robotics, aerospace\n\n - Strong experience working with contract manufacturers, including design release, documentation control, build readiness, on-site collaboration, and ramp-to-mass-production execution.\n\n - BS or higher in mechanical engineering from an accredited engineering program with emphasis on mechanical, machine, structural design fundamentals\n\nThe salary for this position ranges from $200,000-$240,000 per year, depending on experience and qualifications.\n\nWhy ALSO.\n\nWe’re passionate about helping the world find a better way to get there—wherever it is you’re headed.\n\nWe’re located in the heart of Silicon Valley and have brought together a world-class team from some of the biggest brands in the technology, automotive, cycling, outdoor recreation and retail spaces. \n\nTogether we’re working hands-on to imagine, design and build an entirely new solution to a global set of transportation challenges. \n\nPerks and Benefits\n\n - Robust health coverage. Excellent health, dental and vision insurance covered up to 100% by ALSO with FSA \u0026 HSA options.\n\n - One Medical membership and dedicated insurance advocates.\n\n - Rich fertility and family building benefits with Progyny.\n\n - Flexible time off. \n\n - 401(k) match.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
